7%20million%20to%20enhance%20AI%20security%2C%20offering%20tools%20like%20Agentic%20Radar%20for%20protection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company%20tests%20for%20security%20vulnerabilities%20and%20edits%20system%20prompts%20to%20be%20safer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIts%20CEO%20believes%20GenAI%20gives%20cyber%20attackers%20an%20edge%2C%20and%20companies%20must%20vet%20technology%20earlier.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hype-train-profits-valuations-startups-google-openai-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eracing%20to%20adopt%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20pursuit%20of%20productivity%20and%20profits%2C%20but%20the%20last%20thing%20anyone%20wants%20is%20a%20chatbot%20going%20off%20the%20rails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20systems%20are%20vulnerable%20to%20all%20kinds%20of%20new%20threats%2C%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdata-poisoning-ai-chatbot-chatgpt-large-language-models-florain-tramer-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%20poisoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20adversarial%20attacks.%20In%20a%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20survey%20of%20over%20200%20business%20leaders%20in%202023%2C%20more%20than%20half%20said%20generative%20AI%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewould%20give%20cyber%20attackers%20an%20overall%20advantage%20in%20the%20coming%20two%20years%2C%20while%20just%20under%209%25%20said%20that%20advantage%20would%20go%20to%20the%20defenders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20now%20two%20years%20later%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20the%20majority%20of%20those%20business%20leaders%20were%20right%3A%20AI%20has%20given%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbanks-ai-cybersecurity-threats-hackers-generative-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecyber%20attackers%20the%20upper%20hand%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20a%20recent%20Accenture%20survey%20of%20600%20bank%20cybersecurity%20executives%2C%20four%20in%20five%20said%20generative%20AI%20is%20helping%20hackers%20faster%20than%20banks%20can%20keep%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20companies%20worldwide%20adopt%20AI%2C%20Croatian%20security%20startup%20SplxAI%20wants%20to%20redefine%20how%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethey%20test%20AI%20systems%20for%20vulnerabilities%20by%20preemptively%20targeting%20threats.%20The%20company%20recently%20raised%20%247%20million%20in%20a%20seed%20round%20led%20by%20Launchhub%20Ventures%2C%20with%20participation%20from%20venture%20firms%20Rain%20Capital%2C%20Runtime%20Ventures%2C%20Inovo%2C%20DNV%20Ventures%2C%20and%20South%20Central%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20companies%20do%20this%20now%20is%20through%20red-teaming%2C%20which%20involves%20simulating%20adversarial%20attacks%20on%20an%20AI%20system.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-elon-musk-grok-red-team-hiring-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered-teaming%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20often%20take%20a%20few%20weeks%20or%20even%20months%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20racing%20to%20vet%20tools%20before%20they%20deploy%20them%2C%20SplxAI's%20CEO%20Kristian%20Kamber%20told%20BI.%20The%20company%20takes%20an%20offensive%20approach%20by%20adjusting%20system%20prompts%20%E2%80%94%20guidelines%20that%20shape%20how%20an%20AI%20model%20responds%20to%20user%20queries%20%E2%80%94%20reducing%20the%20need%20for%20additional%20defensive%20guardrails%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20clients%20connect%20to%20SplxAI's%20platform%2C%20the%20company%20sends%20them%20a%20questionnaire%20to%20understand%20what%20risk%20means%20to%20them.%20They%20ask%20questions%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20there%20any%20questions%20your%20chatbot%20should%20not%20answer%3F%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BWhich%20parts%20of%20the%20system%20prompt%20are%20confidential%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FElin.AI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElin.AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20a%20chatbot%20geared%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-most-rejected-generation-college-careers-jobs-dating-ghosting-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bneeds%20to%20do%20swearing%20because%20it%20needs%20to%20speak%20the%20language%20of%20the%20kids%2C%26quot%3B%20Kamber%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20SplxAI%20customizes%20its%20approach%2C%20it%20runs%20a%20series%20of%20attacks.%20It%20can%20run%20over%202%2C000%20attacks%20and%2017%20scans%20in%20less%20than%20an%20hour.%20These%20include%20prompt%20injection%20attacks%2C%20in%20which%20AI%20systems%20are%20fed%20malicious%20prompts%20to%20check%20for%20profanity%2C%20misinformation%2C%20or%20data%20poisoning.%20It%20runs%20tests%20to%20check%20for%20bias%2C%20harmful%20content%2C%20or%20intentional%20misuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKamber%20said%20the%20tests%20have%20revealed%20a%20wealth%20of%20bias%2C%20misinformation%2C%20and%20vulnerabilities%20in%20the%20technology%20companies%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESplxAI%20ran%20tests%20on%20a%20popular%20workplace%20productivity%20tool%20that%20revealed%20it%20could%20let%20data%20leak%20between%20colleagues.%20Its%20tests%20on%20a%20healthcare%20company%20that%20operates%20chatbots%20at%20pharmacies%20revealed%20that%20the%20bots%20hallucinated%20when%20giving%20medical%20instructions.%20They%20told%20patients%20to%20take%20pills%20at%20the%20wrong%20times%20or%20offered%20incorrect%20instructions%20on%20how%20to%20use%20injection%20needles.%20It%20uncovered%20gender%20bias%20in%20a%20chatbot%20that%20provided%20career%20advice%20to%20students.%20The%20bot%20told%20young%20women%20to%20pursue%20careers%20as%20secretaries%20and%20young%20men%20to%20pursue%20careers%20as%20business%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20its%20tests%2C%20SplxAI%20generates%20a%20report%20that%20lists%20the%20vulnerabilities%20of%20a%20system%20and%20its%20suggestions%20for%20fixing%20them.%20But%20the%20company%20goes%20a%20step%20further%20by%20changing%20system%20prompts.%