importers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20devastating%2C%20but%20small%20businesses%20have%20a%20worse%20ability%20to%20manage%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Wayne%20Winegarden%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Pacific%20Research%20Institute%2C%20a%20free-market%20think%20tank%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20pro-Main%20Street%2C%20this%20is%20anti-Main%20Street.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20larger%20companies%20are%20in%20a%20better%20position%20to%20absorb%20some%20of%20the%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Winegarden.%20%26quot%3BThey%20have%20probably%20more%20fat%20that%20they%20can%20cut%20than%20small%20businesses.%20Small%20businesses%20operate%20in%20lower%20margins%2C%20so%20they%20can't%20really%20absorb%20it%20as%20easily.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinegarden%20said%20a%20lot%20of%20small%20businesses%20are%20family-owned%2C%20and%20are%20the%20classic%20example%20of%20how%20Americans%20climb%20the%20economic%20ladder%20to%20middle%20class%2C%20upper%20middle%20class%2C%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20tariffs%20just%20cut%20off%20rungs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20said%20Americans%20could%20feel%20%26quot%3Bshort-term%26quot%3B%20pain%20as%20a%20result%20of%20tariffs%2C%20but%20experts%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20that%20pain%20may%20not%20be%20short-term%20for%20everyone%2C%20and%20that%20it's%20the%20small%20businesses%20that%20will%20go%20out%20of%20business%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20temporary%20for%20Starbucks.%20They%20will%20withstand%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Winegarden%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20it's%20a%20year%2C%20that's%20probably%20too%20long%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20small%20businesses%2C%20and%20that's%20permanent%20pain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c9ac53f2-157e-4551-84c4-9d00af580664%5C%22%3EWhy%20small%20businesses%20struggle%20more%20with%20tariffs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Toys%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6802fd1dc6ad288d147ea240%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EToy%20stores%20could%20be%20hit%20hard%20by%20tariffs%2C%20as%20most%20toys%20imported%20to%20the%20US%20are%20made%20in%20China.%3Cp%3EYing%20Tang%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJason%20Miller%2C%20a%20Michigan%20State%20University%20professor%20and%20expert%20in%20supply%20chain%20management%2C%20told%20BI%20there%20were%20several%20factors%20that%20make%20tariffs%20harder%20for%20small%20businesses.%20For%20one%2C%20their%20cash%20flow%20is%20more%20limited%2C%20meaning%20they%20aren't%20necessarily%20able%20to%20pay%20a%20tariff%20for%20a%20product%20that%20they%20won't%20actually%20sell%20until%20some%20point%20in%20the%20future%2C%20sometimes%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20retailers%20are%20also%20less%20likely%20to%20source%20directly%20from%20vendors%20and%20instead%20rely%20on%20an%20intermediary%20like%20a%20wholesaler%20or%20importer.%20That%20gives%20them%20far%20less%20leverage%20to%20negotiate%20prices%20on%20their%20goods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20in%20a%20take%20it%20or%20leave%20it%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20a%20huge%20buyer%20like%20Walmart%20has%20a%20lot%20more%20options%20and%20negotiating%20power%20to%20get%20better%20deals%20on%20the%20products%20they%20sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20said%20toy%20stores%20stand%20out%20to%20him%20as%20a%20sector%20of%20small%20businesses%20that%20could%20be%20especially%20hard%20hit%20by%20the%20tariffs%20on%20China%2C%20where%2080%25%20of%20all%20toy%20imports%20to%20the%20US%20come%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOwners%20of%20independent%2C%20brick-and-mortar%20bridal%20shops%2C%20a%20common%20fixture%20on%20main%20streets%2C%20previously%20told%20BI%20they%20are%20also%20being%20hit%20hard%2C%20as%20a%20majority%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftariffs-trump-china-wedding-dresses-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewedding%20dresses%3C%2Fa%3E%20sold%20in%20the%20US%20come%20from%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20David's%20Bridal%20CEO%20Kelly%20Cook%20said%20the%20company%2C%20which%20is%20the%20largest%20bridal%20retailer%20in%20the%20US%2C%20was%20more%20tariff-resilient%20thanks%20to%20its%20larger%20and%20more%20varied%20supply%20chain%20and%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Cohan%2C%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Babson%20College%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI%20that%20the%20pain%20small%20players%20on%20Main%20Street%20are%20feeling%20would%20likely%20exacerbate%20the%20existing%20trends%20toward%20market%20concentration%2C%20with%20cascading%20effects%20on%20prices%2C%20innovation%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20economic%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSmall%20retailers%20employ%20nearly%20half%20of%20all%20US%20private-sector%20workers.%20Their%20decline%20would%20eliminate%20jobs%20disproportionately%20in%20local%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cohan.%20%26quot%3BConcentrated%20employers%20can%20suppress%20wages.%20Retail%20giants%20like%20Walmart%20have%20been%20linked%20to%20lower%20wages%20in%20local%20labor%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohan%20added%20that%20the%20tariffs%20could%20push%20out%20local%20retailers%20and%20allow%20large%20corporates%20to%20expand%20unchecked%2C%20which%20hurts%20competition%20for%20consumers%20and%20workers.%20Walmart's%20rapid%20expansion%20between%201990%20and%202010%20was%20often%20associated%20with%20the%20decline%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbaby-store-stroller-car-seat-more-expensive-price-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elocal%20retailers%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20the%20same%20region%2C%20and%20Amazon's%20rise%20is%20similarly%20associated%20with%20the%20reduction%20of%20local%20bookstores%2C%20which%20diminished%20diversity%20in%20the%20publishing%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDominant%20retailers%20use%20their%20buying%20power%20to%20demand%20lower%20prices%20from%20suppliers%2C%20but%20these%20savings%20are%20rarely%20passed%20to%20consumers.%20Instead%2C%20suppliers%20may%20cut%20quality%20or%20reduce%20wages%20to%20meet%20demands%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cohan.%20%26quot%3BProfits%20would%20concentrate%20among%20shareholders%20of%20large%20firms%2C%20worsening%20wealth%20gaps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c726fd33-a4ab-4592-acee-cc8fd816fc92%5C%22%3EImporters%20directly%20serving%20retailers%20are%20struggling%2C%20too%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wine%20rack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6802fcc3a466d2b74ab3a564%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWine%20importers%20are%20among%20the%20small%20businesses%20being%20hit%20by%20tariffs.%3Cp%3EDeb%20Cohn-Orbach%2FUCG%2FUniversal%20Images%20Group%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20announced%20widespread%20tariffs%20on%20April%202%2C%20Victor%20Schwartz%20and%20his%20daughter%20Chloe%20Schwartz%2C%20who%20owns%20and%20runs%20VOS%20Selections%2C%20a%20specialty%20wine%20and%20spirits%20importing%20company%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20spent%20the%20next%20two%20days%20in%20an%20intense%20math%20marathon%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20re-price%20their%20products%20%E2%80%94%20and%20which%20ones%20to%20give%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20later%2C%20Trump%20decided%20to%20pause%20so-called%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20on%20most%20trading%20partners%20for%2090%20days%20but%20left%20a%2010%25%20baseline%20rate%20in%20place%2C%20and%20the%20Schwartzs'%20efforts%20immediately%20disappeared%20into%20the%20wind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20that%20position%20of%20having%20to%20make%20firm%20decisions%20about%20what%20our%20pricing%20was%20going%20to%20be%20under%20very%20uncertain%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20Victor%20Schwartz%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThis%20means%20we%20have%20to%20be%20much%20tighter%20in%20our%20inventory.%20We%20had%20to%20reduce%20some%20orders%20where%20we%20could%2C%20we%20stopped%20some%20orders%20where%20we%20could%2C%20we%20didn't%20move%20forward%20on%20new%20projects%20or%20we%20delayed%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20a%20small%2C%20owner-operated%20company%20of%20just%2019%20employees%2C%20VOS%20Selections%20handles%20around%20600%20products%20from%20350%20different%20producers%20around%20the%20world.%20Its%20vast%20portfolio%20used%20to%20be%20a%20merit%2C%20yet%20under%20constantly%20changing%20tariff%20rates%2C%20it%20became%20more%20of%20a%20nightmare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbourbon-whiskey-tariffs-europe-canada-trump-trade-war-prices-cost-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlcohol%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20heavily%20regulated%20product%2C%20and%20regulations%20mandate%20that%20importers%20report%20their%20prices%20at%20least%20one%20month%20ahead%20of%20time%20before%20anything%20reaches%20retailers%20%E2%80%94%20prices%20importers%20cannot%20change%20later.%20For%20Schwartz%2C%20this%20means%20deciding%20prices%20for%20May%20in%20March%2C%20leaving%20room%20for%20supplier%20negotiations%2C%20shipping%20delays%2C%20and%20port%20processing.%20Any%20surprise%20expenses%20in%20this%20process%2C%20such%20as%20a%20sudden%20change%20in%20tariffs%2C%20would%20spell%20disaster%20for%20a%20small%20business%20with%20limited%20cash%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20surprise%20expenses%20aren't%20the%20only%20concern%2C%20said%20Schwartz.%20Retail%20stores%20and%20restaurants%20that%20buy%20wines%20from%20him%20haven't%20been%20doing%20well%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20under%20dampened%20consumer%20sentiments%20and%20other%20tariff-associated%20costs%2C%20which%20he%20said%20caused%20his%20business%20to%20be%20down%2016%25%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20first%20quarter%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20restaurant%20has%20a%20%2420%20price%20point%20for%20their%20white%20wine%2C%20and%20I%20can%20no%20longer%20offer%20it%20at%20%2420%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20buy%20something%20else%2C%20and%20I'll%20lose%20that%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Schwartz.%20%26quot%3BThe%20customer%20that%20was%20paying%20%2420%2C%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20say%20'yes%2C%20we%20really%20liked%20that%20wine%2C%20so%20we're%20willing%20to%20pay%20%2424%20for%20it.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20an%20inflexibility%20in%20pricing%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20the%20customer%20is%20looking%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchwartz's%20business%20is%20now%20the%20lead%20plaintiff%20in%20the%20broadest%20lawsuit%20yet%20against%20Trump's%20use%20of%20the%20International%20Emergency%20Economic%20Powers%20Act%20to%20impose%20tariffs%2C%20which%20no%20prior%20president%20has%20done.%20The%20lawsuit%20argues%20that%20Trump's%20use%20of%20the%20IEEPA%20to%20completely%20bypass%20Congress%20violates%20constitutional%20limits%20on%20executive%20power%2C%20and%20that%20a%20decadelong%20trade%20deficit%20does%20not%20meet%20the%20%26quot%3Bunusual%20and%20extraordinary%20threat%26quot%3B%20criteria%20in%20the%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20April%2018%2C%20the%20Liberty%20Justice%20Center%2C%20a%20Libertarian%20legal%20group%20that%20is%20representing%20this%20lawsuit%20in%20court%2C%20has%20filed%20an%20application%20with%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20International%20Trade%20for%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20to%20suspend%20Trump's%20tariffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinegarden%2C%20from%20the%20Pacific%20Research%20Institute%2C%20said%20he%20is%20concerned%20that%20the%20tariffs%20would%20do%20what%20COVID%20did%20to%20small%20businesses.%20Where%20Winegarden%20lived%20in%20New%20York%2C%20the%20storefronts%20that%20closed%20down%20during%20the%20pandemic%20have%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eremained%20shuttered%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20talks%20about%20small%20businesses%2C%20right%3F%20They're%20the%20heroes%2C%26quot%3B%20Winegarden%20said.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20liked%20small%20businesses%2C%20so%20it's%20just%20so%20ironic.%20Why%20are%20we%20implementing%20policies%20that%20punish%20them%20in%20particular%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20how%20tariffs%20are%20affecting%20your%20small%20business%3F%20Contact%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akatherineli%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekatherineli%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmain-street-trump-trade-war-tariffs-small-businesses-impact-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1745071154000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67fff812c6ad288d147e557b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmain-street-trump-trade-war-tariffs-small-businesses-impact-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Small%20businesses%20told%20BI%20they're%20being%20hit%20hard%20by%20tariffs%20even%20though%20the%20White%20House%20says%20its%20policies%20are%20for%20%26quot%3BMain%20Street%2C%20not%20Wall%20Street.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40businessinsider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CKatherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A88%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.c