stormed%20which%20method%20would%20be%20most%20cost-effective%20for%20getting%20my%20family%20and%20me%20to%20Utah%20in%20time%20for%20the%20funeral.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it%20was%20the%20kindness%20of%20a%20family%20friend%2C%20who%20lent%20us%20his%20large%20four-wheel%20drive%20vehicle%20and%20his%20gas%20card%2C%20that%20allowed%20us%20to%20make%20the%20trip%20to%20Utah.%20It%20was%20a%20true%20act%20of%20heroism%20that%20I've%20never%20forgotten.%20We%20drove%2024%20hours%20straight%20through%20the%20mountains%20and%20snow%2C%20arriving%20in%20time%20for%20the%20funeral%20and%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20my%20beloved%20grandpa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20experience%20changed%20how%20I%20manage%20my%20money%2C%20including%20keeping%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fwhat-is-an-emergency-fund%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemergency%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20a%20separate%20emergency%20fund%20in%20a%20bank%20account%2C%20but%20I%20also%20keep%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fhow-to-earn-redeem-southwest-points%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthwest%20points%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20all%20times%20for%20emergency%20flights.%20Unlike%20a%20cash%20emergency%20account%2C%20my%20airline%20points%20aren't%20useful%20for%20broken%20household%20appliances%2C%20car%20repairs%2C%20or%20surprise%20medical%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20emergency%20fund%20operates%20similarly%20to%20a%20sinking%20fund%20in%20my%20household.%20While%20we%20occasionally%20use%20the%20points%20for%20leisure%20trips%20or%20family%20vacations%2C%20we%20make%20sure%20to%20keep%20a%20high%20balance%2C%20usually%20between%2050%2C000%20and%20100%2C000%20points%20at%20all%20times%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20good%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee4fb4ee-4a81-4102-8b36-bf370f62e954%5C%22%3ESouthwest%20points%20are%20flexible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESouthwest%20points%20don't%20expire%2C%20which%20means%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20using%20my%20points%20this%20month%20or%20this%20year.%20Similar%20to%20a%20bank%20account%2C%20I'm%20able%20to%20earn%20and%20store%20my%20points%20until%20I'm%20ready%20to%20use%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20purchase%20a%20flight%20using%20Southwest%20points%2C%20you%20can%20cancel%20the%20flight%20%3Cspan%3Eup%20to%2010%20minutes%20before%20the%20scheduled%20departure%20time%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20get%20all%20of%20your%20points.%20This%20is%20particularly%20helpful%20when%20you%20are%20dealing%20with%20delicate%20situations%20like%20the%20birth%20of%20a%20baby%20or%20when%20plans%20change%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlights%20purchased%20with%20cash%20can%20be%20changed%20but%20usually%20for%20a%20fee.%20Sometimes%20you%20only%20receive%20a%20flight%20credit%2C%20not%20an%20actual%20refund.%20When%20you%20buy%20a%20flight%20with%20points%2C%20you%20can%20simply%20cancel%20it%20and%20the%20points%20will%20be%20credited%20back%20to%20your%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9eaad23-31b2-4812-b7be-2821729841dd%5C%22%3EI%20can%20use%20points%20without%20having%20to%20dip%20into%20my%20cash%20emergency%20fund%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20get%20notice%20of%20a%20death%20or%20medical%20emergency%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20to%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20is%20money.%20But%20traveling%2C%20especially%20with%20little%20notice%2C%20can%20be%20expensive.%20Hotels%2C%20rental%20cars%2C%20and%20food%20costs%20add%20up%20quickly.%20Since%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20use%20my%20cash%20reserves%20to%20pay%20for%20my%20flight%2C%20my%20costs%20are%20significantly%20reduced.%20I%20can%20focus%20on%20my%20family%20member%20or%20friend%20who%20I%20am%20there%20to%20support%2C%20rather%20than%20worrying%20about%20the%20cost%20of%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20there%20have%20been%20times%20when%20my%20cash%20emergency%20fund%20has%20been%20depleted%20quickly%20for%20other%20things%2C%20leaving%20me%20with%20low%20funds.%20Once%2C%20we%20had%20%242%2C400%20worth%20of%20car%20repairs%20in%2024%20hours.%20If%20an%20emergency%20popped%20up%20where%20I%20needed%20to%20travel%20and%20I%20%3Cem%3Edidn't%3C%2Fem%3E%20have%20my%20points%20reserve%2C%20I%20would've%20been%20much%20more%20worried%20about%20traveling%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225f33b2ae-6c60-4e12-b872-4d8eb405f61f%5C%22%3EI%20can%20use%20them%20365%20days%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20no%20blackout%20dates%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20Christmas%2C%20my%20sister%20got%20devastating%20news%20that%20her%20mother-in-law%20had%20died%20in%20the%20early%20morning%20hours.%20Her%20husband%20was%20able%20to%20get%20a%20standby%20ticket%20from%20a%20friend%20who%20worked%20for%20an%20airline%2C%20but%20purchasing%20a%20flight%20for%20her%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20from%20Utah%20to%20New%20York%20%E2%80%94%20would've%20been%20a%20huge%20expense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20my%20Southwest%20points%20balance%20was%20over%20100%2C000.%20I%20purchased%20her%20a%20ticket%2C%20and%20she%20was%20able%20to%20fly%20out%20the%20next%20day%20to%20be%20with%20her%20husband%20and%20his%20family%20without%20costing%20me%20or%20her%20much%20of%20anything.%20(Yes%2C%20we%20still%20had%20to%20pay%20the%20government%20fees%20of%20%2411.20%20per%20flight%2C%20but%20the%20actual%20flight%20cost%20was%20%240.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6a1f4a2-83d0-409d-b350-0486af58989e%5C%22%3EI%20can%20use%20my%20Southwest%20credit%20card%20and%20the%20shopping%20portal%20to%20earn%20points%20quickly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20had%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fcredit-cards%2Fchase-southwest-rapid-rewards-premier-credit-card-review%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESouthwest%20credit%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%202014%20when%20my%20grandfather%20died%2C%20and%2